{"word":"ὀλβίζω","slug":"ὀλβίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀλβίζω</b></el> <el>(ὀλβίζω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὄλβιος'><el>ὄλβιος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to make happy</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <i>to deem</i> or <i>pronounce happy</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be</i> or <i>be deemed happy</i>, <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>ὠλβισμένοι</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; aor1 <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>ὀλβισθείς</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}